## Step 2: Funnel Flow Modeling

### Project ToFU Volume

Start with forecasted ToFU leads per channel. Sources for projections:

| Projection Method | When to Use |
|-------------------|-------------|
| **Historical trend** | Stable channels, no major changes |
| **Spend-based** | Paid channels with known efficiency |
| **Capacity-based** | Limited inventory (events, partnerships) |
| **Growth target** | New channels with investment plans |

```ruby
# Example: Project ToFU leads
def project_tofu_leads(channel, forecast_period)
  historical = historical_tofu_leads(channel, lookback_days: 90)
  monthly_average = historical / 3.0  # 90 days = 3 months

  case projection_method(channel)
  when :historical_trend
    apply_trend(monthly_average, channel.growth_rate)
  when :spend_based
    channel.forecasted_spend / channel.cost_per_first_touch
  when :growth_target
    monthly_average * (1 + channel.target_growth)
  end
end
```

