### Adjust for Channel Overlap

If participation data shows high channel interdependence, adjust the forecast:

```ruby
def apply_overlap_adjustment(channel_forecasts, participation_data)
  # If participation sum >> 100%, channels work together
  # Isolated forecasts will overestimate total

  participation_sum = participation_data.values.sum  # e.g., 180%
  overlap_factor = 1.0 / (participation_sum / 100.0)  # e.g., 0.56

  # Don't apply full adjustmentвҖ”channels still have independent value
  adjustment = 1 - ((1 - overlap_factor) * 0.5)  # e.g., 0.78

  channel_forecasts.transform_values do |forecast|
    forecast * adjustment
  end
end
```

<%= render_warning_box do %>
  <strong>Overlap warning:</strong> If participation credits sum to 180%, your channels are heavily interdependent. Forecasts assuming channel independence will overpredict revenue. Apply an overlap adjustment of 10-25%.
<% end %>

## Step 3: Revenue Calculation

### Sum Channel-Level Revenue

```ruby
def calculate_total_forecast(channel_forecasts)
  channel_forecasts.sum do |channel, data|
    data[:forecasted_conversions] * data[:aov]
  end
end

# With confidence intervals
def forecast_with_range(channel_forecasts, confidence: 0.80)
  base = calculate_total_forecast(channel_forecasts)

  # Historical variance determines range
  historical_variance = calculate_historical_variance(channel_forecasts)

  {
    forecast: base,
    low: base * (1 - historical_variance),
    high: base * (1 + historical_variance),
    confidence: confidence
  }
end
```

