## Step 4: Validation & Adjustment

### Back-Test Against History

Test your methodology on historical data before trusting it for forecasts:

```ruby
def backtest_forecast_accuracy(methodology, test_periods: 6)
  results = []

  test_periods.times do |i|
    # Use period N-1 to forecast period N
    training_end = Date.today - ((i + 1) * 30)
    training_start = training_end - 90

    forecast = methodology.forecast(
      training_start: training_start,
      training_end: training_end,
      forecast_period: 30
    )

    # Compare to actual
    actual = actual_revenue(
      start_date: training_end,
      end_date: training_end + 30
    )

    results << {
      period: training_end,
      forecast: forecast,
      actual: actual,
      error: ((forecast - actual).abs / actual * 100).round(1)
    }
  end

  average_error = results.map { |r| r[:error] }.sum / results.size
  { results: results, average_error: average_error }
end
```

### Acceptable Error Ranges

| Error Range | Assessment | Action |
|-------------|------------|--------|
| **< 10%** | Excellent | Model is well-calibrated |
| **10-20%** | Good | Normal variance, monitor trends |
| **20-30%** | Fair | Review assumptions, check for changes |
| **> 30%** | Poor | Recalibrate model, investigate causes |

