### Seasonality Adjustment

Apply historical seasonal patterns:

```ruby
def apply_seasonality(base_forecast, target_month)
  # Historical seasonal indices (1.0 = average)
  seasonal_index = {
    1 => 0.85,   # January: post-holiday dip
    2 => 0.90,
    3 => 0.95,
    4 => 1.00,
    5 => 1.05,
    6 => 1.00,
    7 => 0.95,
    8 => 0.95,
    9 => 1.00,
    10 => 1.05,
    11 => 1.15,  # November: pre-holiday surge
    12 => 1.20   # December: peak
  }

  base_forecast * seasonal_index[target_month]
end
```

